think about it, every single aspect, every organ in your body has a voltage across it, across the
outer boundary, the epidermis or the outer layer of the organ that the kidney does. It has an outer
envelope, the liver. And there's a voltage across each one. And that voltage is important for the
function of that organ. So we are electric beings, that's for sure. And it's something that's
very, very slow to be realized by the medical community or anybody else, really.
